  "text": "Another possible cause of Oligo-Miocene igneous activity in southern Tibet suggested by [CITATION_1] is lithospheric-scale rifting, whereby large, deep cracks in the mantle lithosphere allow asthenosphere to flow upward, providing the necessary heat for melt production. Alternatively, the ϳ21 Ma granites could be related to slab break-off, slab detachment, or a Gangdese Thrust event, similar to the 24 to 26 Ma granites further southeast.",
